{{recipe}}
==Ingredients== * Mushroom, sliced 60g * [[Cookbook:Butter|Butter]], 10g * [[Cookbook:Flour|Flour]] 10 g * Dried onion 15 g * [[Cookbook:Bay Leaf|Bay leaf]] 2 leaves * Milk or white stock 180 ml * Seasoning to taste * Cream 20 ml * Brunoise cut of mushroom for garnish * Parsley
==Procedure== # Heat the butter in a heavy sauce pot or pan, add chopped onion and mushroom stir for few seconds until just transparent. Don't let the mushroom brown. # Then add flour, stir to make roux. Don't let them brown, then pour over milk or white stock, bring to boil. # Simmer the soup for 10 to 15 minutes until mushroom is cooked # Pass the soup through a food mill or into a blender to purée it # Add the purée of mushroom into the soup and add enough hot milk or cream to the soup to bring it to proper consistency but do not boil. # Season to taste, garnish with brunoise cut of mushroom and parsley

== Task 1: The Solar System ==

Below are the eight planets of our solar system, each with a description.  Fill in the blanks in the descriptions.

* First you have to fill in which planet it is from the sun. For example: if you think Jupiter is the seventh planet, fill in ''7th''.
* Secondly you have to fill in if the planet is bigger or smaller than Earth. The bigger/smaller question for Earth is about the moon!

{| class="wikitable"
|- valign="top"
| width="5" | [[Image:Venus-real color.jpg|thumb|90px|Venus is the '''2nd''' planet of our Solar System and it's '''smaller''' than Earth.]]
| width="5" | [[Image:The Earth seen from Apollo 17.jpg|thumb|90px|Earth is the '''3rd''' planet of our Solar System and the moon is '''smaller''' than Earth.]]
| width="5" | [[Image:Jupiter.jpg|thumb|90px|Jupiter is the '''5th''' planet of our Solar System and it's '''bigger''' than Earth.]]
| width="5" | [[File:Saturn.png|thumb|90px|Saturn is the '''6th''' planet of our Solar System and it's '''bigger''' than Earth.]]
| width="5" | [[File:Neptune Full.jpg|thumb|90px|Neptune is the '''8th''' planet of our Solar System and it's '''bigger''' than Earth.]]
| width="5" | [[Image:File-Uranus, Earth size comparison without Earth.png|thumb|90px|Uranus is the '''7th''' planet of our Solar System and it's '''bigger''' than Earth.]]
| width="5" | [[Image:Mercury-real color.jpg|thumb|90px|Mercury is the '''1st''' planet of our Solar System and it's '''smaller''' than Earth.]]
| width="5" | [[Image:Mars Hubble.jpg|thumb|90px|Mars is the '''4th''' planet of our Solar System and it's '''smaller''' than Earth.]]
|}

''8 points can be earned with this task.  Every wrong sentence reduces the score by 1.

== Task 2: About the planets ==

{{question-answer|question=Is Mercury hot everywhere?|answer=No (it's cold in the shadow).}}
{{question-answer|question=Why does Venus appear to us to shine like a star?|answer=There are clouds hanging above Venus which reflect the sunlight.}}
{{question-answer|question=How many kilometres from the Sun is Earth?|answer=About 150 million.}}
{{question-answer|question=Why is it so cold on Mars?|answer=It's so far from the sun.}}
{{question-answer|question=What is the Great Red Spot on Jupiter?|answer=A storm.}}
{{question-answer|question=What are the rings of Saturn like?|answer=Sand, rocks, and ice.}}
{{question-answer|question=Is Uranus the only planet standing straight up?|answer=No (actually it's on its side).}}
{{question-answer|question=Is there water on Neptune?|answer=No (Neptune is named after the Roman god of the seas, but there is no water on Neptune).}}

''8 points can be earned with this task. Every right answer gives 1 point.''

