This book will show: # How to make a CAPTCHA # Typical CAPTCHA usages
== Chapters == * [[/Why?/]] * [[/Usages/]] * [[/Integration/]] **[[/Integration/Pre-made|Pre-made]] **[[/Integration/Roll your own|Roll your own]] ***[[/Integration/The Anti-CAPTCHA|The Anti-CAPTCHA]] ****[[/Integration/The Anti-CAPTCHA/Stronger|The Anti-CAPTCHA - Stronger]] ***[[/Integration/Images and PHP|Images and PHP]] **[[/Integration/Plugins for software|Plugins]] * [[/Conclusion/]]
{{subjects|Internet}} {{alphabetical|C}} {{status|75%}}

This is a CAPTCHA killer. It needs nothing on the form except a hidden field and some server-side code. 

