== SOC 101 - Introduction to Sociology == === Seattle Central Community College === :[[Introduction to Sociology/Noted Contributors]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Famous Sociologists]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Sociological Methods]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Sociological Theory]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Culture]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Socialization]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Family]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Education]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Groups]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Deviance]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Stratification]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Race and Ethnicity]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Gender]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Sexuality]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Health and Medicine]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Collective Behavior]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Social Movements]] :[[Introduction to Sociology/Being a Sociologist]]
[[Category:Collections|SCCC-SOC 101]]

Here is a good starting vocabulary list to learn.
This is the wordlist given at the start of Vere aŭ Fantazie, by Claude Piron. It is the 400 or so words that a beginner should know after completing a beginner’s textbook or course, such as Gerda Malaperis. Piron assumes that you will already know all these words before starting to read Vere aŭ Fantazie, his collection of tales for progressing beginners.
http://en.lernu.net/biblioteko/rakontoj/vere_aux_fantazie/vortoj.php
