== Vav ==

There is in fact no letter Vav in Hebrew. There is a Waw, which European Jews wouldn't pronounce. Likewise don't teach Ayin  only as like Aleph when it is actually the same as Ayn in Arabic, but again, European Jews would not pronounce it. Then there's Hhet like in the Arabic word Wahhad (one) and Hebrew Ehhad which is mispronounced as Echad as in the German sprache. The there's Rimel whis is like the Arabic Ghayin. &c
